"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The 'roc_curve' function is being used with multiclass classification output without binarizing the output first. The 'y_score' variable has shape (45, 3) indicating it is a multiclass classification output. According to the scikit-learn guideline for Multiclass Receiver Operating Characteristic API, 'ROC curves are typically used in binary classification, where the TPR and FPR can be defined unambiguously. In the case of multiclass classification, a notion of TPR or FPR is obtained only after binarizing the output.'\", \"patch\": \"29c29\\n<     fpr[i], tpr[i], thresh = roc_curve(y_test, y_score, pos_label=i)\\n---\\n>     fpr[i], tpr[i], thresh = roc_curve(y_onehot_test[:, i], y_score[:, i])\\n\"}"